## Field of Study: Evolutionary Educational Psychology

This is a rather niche intersection, you see. It’s where the inherent, almost instinctual ways humans learn—the stuff hardwired by millennia of evolution—collides with the decidedly unnatural environments we’ve constructed for formal education, like [schools](/School) and the soul-crushing industrial [workplace](/Workplace). It’s about understanding how our ancient minds process new information in contexts that are, frankly, alien to our ancestral past. It's part of a larger, frankly overwhelming, landscape of [Psychology](/Psychology), a field that attempts to map the labyrinth of the human psyche.

